The '''Anim''' or '''Fly River''' languages are a group of [[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] families in south-central New Guinea established by Usher & Suter (2015).<ref>Timothy Usher and Edgar Suter (2015) "The Anim Languages of Southern New Guinea". ''Oceanic Linguistics'' 54:110–142</ref>

==Languages==
The languages are as follows:<ref>https://sites.google.com/site/newguineaworld/families/trans-new-guinea/fly-river</ref> 

*[[Inland Gulf languages|Inland Gulf]]
*[[Tirio languages|Tirio]] (Lower Fly River)
*[[Boazi languages|Boazi]] (Lake Murray)
*[[Marind languages|Marind]] (Marind–Yaqai)

The [[Abom language]], previously considered a member of the Tirio family, is of uncertain classification within Trans–New Guinea, but do not appear to be Anim.

